fields.description:
When specifying include and exclude information for tree processing, complex path configuration doesn't seem possible. The goal here is to do the following:

{noformat}
#include //DEPOT/mainline/
#include //DEPOT/releases/
#exclude //DEPOT/releases/deprecated-release/
#exclude //DEPOT/sandbox/
#include //DEPOT/sandbox/important-test-project/
{noformat}

Once the sandbox path has been excluded, no subtrees are parsed, even when explicitly included in the Includes section of the repository configuration.

When defining the http bind, in Administration > Server Settings, users can accidently put the full url (including the http) when they should be only putting the hostname;port. 

E.g. 

{code:xml}
<web-server>
        <http bind="http://hostname:8060"/>
</web-server>
{code}

When they should be putting

{code:xml}
<web-server>
        <http bind="hostname:8060"/>
</web-server>
{code}

If they do, do this, then their server cannot start and will have the following error:

{noformat}
ERROR - Unknown host error binding web port: http: http
{noformat}

We should validate the entry to ensure they can't do this (in the Admin UI).
